        <p> When I arrived in Ahrensburg, I picked up Basti and his luggage and we drove straight to the airport. There we got rid of the rental car really quickly and easily. Now we still had plenty of time until boarding. So first we unpacked our sandwiches and had breakfast at the "Restaurant zur Goldenen MÃ¶we". We wanted to check in our luggage two hours before departure. </p>
        <p> PANIC: Something was wrong with my entry confirmation for Canada. When applying for the ETA, I had entered the passport number incorrectly. One O was actually a 0. As we learned, there are no O's in passport numbers. Fortunately, the lady at the counter was able to resolve the problem. Thanks to our excellent preparation, we also passed the security check quickly. </p>
        <p> The flight to London Heathrow was uneventful except for the fact that British Airways now charges for drinks on short-haul flights. When we arrived early in London, we had to go through security again. So we had to unpack all our electronic devices. And we have quite a few of those. </p>

