        <p> At the boarding pass check (which we had on our phones), we got another shock. "Please report to the counter." There we were informed that we had been upgraded to World Traveller Plus class. Super!!! So with grins on our faces, we browsed the Harry Potter shop and then quickly ate some fries. In the waiting area, we tried to put on our compression socks while stifling laughter. Which almost worked. </p>
        <p> Boarding the Boeing 787 to Montreal started with a half-hour delay. We had to take the bus to the plane again. Our seats were great. We could sit together and even stretch our legs. There were pillows, blankets, noise-canceling headphones, and delicious food. And the drinks were included too. So we ordered beer and whiskey to toast our journey. The plane then took off with a 1.5-hour delay at 18:12 because the pushback vehicle was broken. With a bit of tailwind, we landed at 19:52 in Montreal. Local time, of course. Now we have a 6-hour time difference from Germany. </p>
        <p> The entry into Canada went surprisingly smoothly. Scan passport, take photo, written and oral test, and we were already in Canada. </p>
        <p> Now for the most important thing: organizing phone cards for our cell phones. That was quick too, and so the Uber dropped us off at the BestWestern Hotel around 9:30 PM. The room was okay, we wandered around a bit more, and then went to bed right on time at 10:30 PM. </p>
        <p> Good night out there. </p>
